Entry Date: 1. If JE having multiple details then add multiple rows having same 'Default Global Items'/'Global Custom Items' Data and different as per your details of 'Default Line Items'/'Line Level Custom Items'.
2. If 'Account code' is empty then 'Account Name' should be in sample file.
2. If Custom Field Item having 'Multi-Select Drop Down' then the values should differentiate by semicolon (;).
3. If Custom Field Item having 'Check List' then values for the sequence should provide in true/false differentiate by semicolon (;).
4. If Custom Field Item having 'Check Box' then values should be 'true'/'false'.
5. In import wizard pick the right matching  'Date Format'.
6. Exchange Rate should be from other currency to base currency.
7. Remove Comma (,) and extra white spaces in file if exist.
